nts despite having disgraphia and I read constantly. I fell behind in math both years I was public schooled because I lost interest after the first few months of repetition and those two years of public school still stand out as the worst years of my life even ten years later. How many school districts are going to become unaccredited or suffer rape and abuse scandals or bully related suicides or shootings before we realize that this is not how children are meant to be taught? For every homeschooled child that can't do basic algebra I will show you six that outperform public schoolers and two that are dabbling in four dimensional geometry. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="955" language="en" documentId="223" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="Drew W" date="7/29/2013 9:32 PM GMT+0200" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://www.washingtonpost.com/local/students-home-schooling-highlights-debate-over-va-religious-exemption-law/2013/07/28/ee2dbb1a-efbc-11e2-bed3-b9b6fe264871_comment.html?commentID=washingtonpost.com/ECHO/item/1375126331-245-670" topic="homeschooling" thumbsUp="0" thumbsDown="0" origId="223" notes="" title="Student’s home-schooling highlights debate over Va. religious exemption law"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="955"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39"/></xmi:XMI>